  <p>Commercial Property Cleaning (CPC) has delivered professional school cleaning services to Australian primary schools, high schools and special education facilities since 1995, operating across Queensland, New South Wales, Victoria, Western Australia and South Australia.</p>

  <h2>What School Cleaning Requires</h2>
  <p>School cleaning is one of the most compliance-intensive cleaning environments in Australia. Every staff member deployed to a school must hold a current Working With Children Check (WWCC) for the relevant state. Credential renewal must be actively managed throughout the contract — not just verified at commencement.</p>
  <p>Beyond WWCC requirements, school cleaning must meet WHS obligations specific to environments where children are present, manage chemical storage and handling in accordance with school safety requirements, and operate within school hours, after hours and holiday programs without disrupting the learning environment.</p>
  <p>Schools that contract cleaning services without verifying these compliance requirements create direct liability exposure for their principal and governing body.</p>

  <h2>What CPC Delivers for Schools</h2>
  <p>CPC manages WWCC verification and renewal for every staff member deployed to education facilities as a standard operational function — not an exception process. Our credential management system tracks expiry dates and initiates renewal before credentials lapse.</p>
  <p>Our school cleaning services include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Daily classroom and common area cleaning</li>
    <li>Toilet and amenity block cleaning</li>
    <li>Canteen and kitchen cleaning</li>
    <li>Gymnasium and sports facility cleaning</li>
    <li>Administration and staff area cleaning</li>
    <li>Holiday deep cleans aligned to school term schedules</li>
  </ul>
  <p>CPC operates under ISO 9001 quality management certification, ISO 14001 environmental management certification and ISO 45001 occupational health and safety certification. All three certifications are maintained through a JAS-ANZ accredited certification body and are available for verification through CPC's <a href="/due-diligence/compliance-centre/">Due Diligence Hub</a>.</p>

  <h2>Cleaning Chemicals in Schools</h2>
  <p>CPC uses TGA-approved and environmentally responsible cleaning products across all education facilities. Chemical registers are maintained for every school site and are available to school administration on request. Staff are trained in chemical handling specific to environments where children may be present.</p>

  <h2>Holiday and Deep Clean Programs</h2>
  <p>School holidays provide the primary opportunity for deep cleaning that cannot be completed during term. CPC coordinates holiday cleaning programs aligned to each school's term calendar, covering:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Carpet steam cleaning</li>
    <li>High-level dusting</li>
    <li>Hard floor stripping and resealing</li>
    <li>Thorough cleaning of areas that receive heavy use during term</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Compliance Documentation for Schools</h2>
  <p>Principals and business managers responsible for facilities procurement can access CPC's full compliance documentation through the <a href="/due-diligence/">Due Diligence Hub</a>, including current ISO certificates, WWCC management process documentation, insurance certificates, modern slavery statement and WHS documentation — without needing to submit a formal request.</p>

  <h2>National Coverage for Education Portfolios</h2>
  <p>CPC services education portfolios ranging from single schools to multi-site networks across state education departments, Catholic education offices and independent school associations. Our national footprint means consistent standards and a single compliance documentation source regardless of how many sites are in your portfolio.</p>
  <p>To discuss school cleaning services for your facility or education portfolio, <a href="/contact/">contact us</a> or call 1300 272 888.</p>

